data.description: Escape to this private and inviting two-story home nestled on 10 fenced acres that is surrounded by mature trees and shrubs. Start your days with breathtaking fresh air and rejuvenating sunrises and unwind at the end with awe-inspiring sunsets and cool evening breezes. This private retreat, about an hour from Fresno, perfect for families seeking a permanent residence or a vacation home. Savvy investors can also turn it into a rental or AirBnB. Several updates have been done through the years. Step onto the covered patio through French doors and discover the first level, featuring a master bedroom with a full bathroom, a spare bedroom, a half bathroom, a laundry room, and a cozy family room. The second level boasts a spacious living room, a full bathroom, a well-equipped kitchen, a dining room, and a charming loft. Access the covered wooden deck from the living room, leading you to a rich garden area awaiting your green thumb. Convenience is key, with a detached two-car carport, a workshop, two storage rooms, and even a chicken coop. On the north side of Buck Canyon Road, you'll find an additional mobile home that has historically been used for storage but has air conditioning and utilities. This serene & secluded property offers the perfect blend of tranquility and accessibility. It's the home of abundant wildlife, including but not limited to turkeys, bobcats, hawks, deer, quail, dove, and rabbits.
